description: Men aged 27 and 34 remain in custody for questioning after being arrested on suspicion of wounding.
title: Two men arrested after suspected Grangetown stabbing
title_page: Two men arrested after suspected Grangetown stabbing - BBC News
maintext:
Two men have been arrested in connection with a suspected stabbing which left the victim in hospital.
Police said it happened on Birchington Avenue in the Grangetown area of Redcar and Cleveland at about 15:30 GMT on Saturday.
Cleveland Police said it had arrested two men - one aged 27 and from the Marton area, the other 34 years old and from Grangetown - on suspicion of Section 18 wounding. A spokesperson said both remained men in custody for questioning.
The 37-year-old victim suffered head and arm injuries which are not believed to be life-threatening, police added.
